Johannesburg City Power JOHANNESBURG - Parts of Roodepoort are in the dark after two City Power transformers burnt down on Saturday morning. READ:Â SA's electricity crisis | Eskom names and shames defaulters The fire is said to have started at around 1am on Saturday, taking down some vital equipment. The fire brigade managed to extinguish the fire around 8am. Unfortunately, areas including Robertsville, Wipsey Dip, Putcoton, and Stormhill are without power. City Power is currently attending to the outage but cannot confirm when electricity will be restored. Investigations are ongoing and the extent of the damage is being assessed. The utility has apologised to affected residents. #RobertvilleOutage #JoburgUpdates#OutageUpdate
